node.title: To the father of my child...😍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 15, 2021.

node.text:
✨After having your baby, it is normal to feel tired and go through some hormonal changes that make you irritable or want to cry. 🙁 If this is your case, don’t worry! These symptoms usually last only a few days. But, if they persist, it is important that you notify your doctor so that they can guide you.👆

#postpartum #postpartumdepression #postpartumdepressionawareness #babyblues  #mentalhealth #beingamom #momlife

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 day self-care challenge every mom should try! kkinedu'.

node.text:
✨💚A good self-care routine can be life-changing. Self-care can help you feel better and reset your mood. This is why it is a must for moms!

👩‍🦰As a mom, you might have experienced feeling exhausted and burnt out.  We know firsthand how hard it is to focus on yourself when your main job is to take care of others.

👆But, once you start to make time for yourself, you will feel so much better, and your whole mindset will change.

#selfcare #selfcareroutine #momroutine #mentalhealth #beingamom #momlife

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7 day self-care challenge every mom should try! kkinedu'.
Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'MONDAY Get moving today! Exercise for a minimum of 20 minutes (go for a walk or do a workout at home). ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TUESDAY Wake up 1 hour before your kid(s). Make your favorite coffee or tea and drink it while doing something you enjoy (read, write, watch a t.v. show, etc.). Kkinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'WEDNESDAY Spend a little extra time getting ready today. Do your hair, put on makeup, and wear an outfit you feel good in (when you look good, it can help you feel good). kinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of fruit and text that says 'THURSDAY Eat fruit for breakfast today. Make a smoothie or chop up some fresh fruit for a quick and healthy breakfast. ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of drink and text that says 'FRIDAY It's the end of the week! Put the kids in bed a little early tonight, and watch your favorite movie or show to unwind. TV lkinedu'.
Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be a cartoon of child and text that says 'SATURDAY Have a lazy day with your kids today. Order take-out and have a movie day with your family! kinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 13, 2021. May be an image of drink and text that says 'SUNDAY Today is all about hydration. Make sure you drink 6-8 cups of water today and limit any sugary drinks. ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Children many times don't ask for love and connection, instead they say something like: Come play with me... I want you to lay with me until fall asleep Can we read one more book during bedtime? ikinedu'.

node.text: ✨Remember that your little one is just learning to communicate what he wants and needs, that is why his way of asking for attention and affection may not seem obvious so it is important that you learn to interpret what he is asking for but above all, it is important that they spend quality time together.

node.text: Without a doubt, one of the most special days in the life of every mom, a single word that has the power to fill you with a thousand feelings. 💚🤍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, book and text that says 'Top 5 back-to-school books for little ones By Molly Dresner ikinedu'.

node.text:
📕🖍Heading back to school can be an exciting, yet anxious time for parents and little ones alike. Books are the best way to prepare us for changes like these! They teach beautiful lessons and open the communication gates so that your child has a chance to ask questions and share their feelings. 

✨Molly Dresner (@thespeechteacher) is a Speech-Language Pathologist based in New York City. She authored The Speech Teacher’s Handbook, an engaging parent guide that includes practical and easy-to-follow tips and activities to help you and your little one!

#booksrecommendation #kidsbooks #backtoschool #literacymatters #booksforchildren #tipsforparents #beingamom #toddlerbooks

May be a cartoon of text that says 'Pout -Pout Fish The ©Material Goes to School S992W998 Deborah Diesen Picturesby Dan Hanna Û hePout-PotFish The Pout-Pout Fish Goes to School Our little pout-pout fish is feeling nervous about their first day of school and is sure that they don't have the know-how to get through the day. After heading nto few wrong classrooms, our brave pout-pout fish finally ends up with the "brand new fish" and learns some brilliant facts! ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 06, 2021. May be a cartoon of book and text that says 'w BESTSELLER KISSING The HAND Audrey Penn The Kissing Hand This sweet story is perfect for little ones who are anxious about being apart from their parents during the school day. Separating for the first time can feel overwhelming for lot of our tiny friends (and us too!) The kissing hand is an adorable little trick that lets us hold onto our loved ones' kiss throughout the day so that we feel connected and safe. kinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 06, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'JANE YOLEN 18 MARK TEAGUE How Dinosaurs to Do School? Go How Do Dinosaurs Go to School We love this book because it is ever so silly, but also creates a wonderful dialogue for how behave school. This story has us wondering about how dinosaur might act throughout the school day -do they interrupt or roar and yell? Your little one will love the funny illustrations and scenarios. 🌟 How exactly do routines help our children and why are they so helpful for them?

1) They foster the development of self-control ☺️
Knowing what comes next gives children security and emotional stability, making them feel more in control.

2) They promote positive behavior
Routines are like a set of steps that guide children towards certain goals 🤩
This can help to ensure children’s safety and help them learn responsible behaviors.

3) They help develop social skills 🤗
Little by little, children start to learn the patterns of social relations and the things that play an important role in them, like sharing, taking turns, and cooperating.

4) They provide learning opportunities 🤓
While adults might find routines boring sometimes, for children, everyday routines are great and fun learning tools. Tell your little one a story about their day! This will help them be aware of their experiences and feelings, making sense of the events in their life.

💙 If you want to learn more about routines and how to use them to stimulate your child’s development, check out kinedu | learn in our Link in Bio!

☀️A morning routine is just as important as a bedtime routine, especially for newborns!

👶Babies thrive in a predictable world, and for good reason —every day is filled with new learning experiences and excitement! That’s why routines for babies will provide them with a sense of safety, comfort, and trust. 

✨Another important factor is that babies don’t understand the concept of time yet, so they organize their lives based on the events that happen during the day. When things happen in the same order, babies have a better understanding of their world!🌎
